author: Sarah D.
title: Oh no she DI’INT! Rachel Dolezal has reportedly changed her name … to this???
text:
— Antwain Booth (@abooth03) March 1, 2017 
For those of you wondering what fake black woman Rachel Dolezal has been up to lately, here’s your answer: First, tried to change her race. Now it appears #RachelDolezal has changed her name. What I found in Spokane Court records. Note case #s . pic.twitter.com/feJXttj8uG 
— Melissa Luck ☘ (@MelissaKXLY4) March 1, 2017 EXCLUSIVE: Rachel Dolezal has legally changed her name to a West African moniker meaning 'gift of god’ https://t.co/l7cLxW4xPG 
— Daily Mail US (@DailyMail) March 1, 2017 Rachel Dolezal Changes Name to West African for 'Gift of God' https://t.co/qet1ZAalRz 
More from the Daily Mail : Rachel Dolezal, the former head of Spokane, Washington’s NAACP chapter who claimed to be black before her parents ‘outed’ her as white, officially changed her name to Nkechi Amare Diallo in a Washington court in October, legal documents obtained by DailyMail.com show. Nkechi, short for Nkechinyere, is a name that originates from the Igbo language of Nigeria and means ‘what god has given’ or ‘gift of god.’ Diallo, meaning ‘bold,’ is a last name of Fula origin. The Fula people are a Muslim ethnic group thought to have roots in the Middle East and North Africa, who are now widely dispersed across West Africa. 
More like Rachel LOL -ezal, are we right?
